02:06:58.78 --> 02:07:06.78
But I knew he would see me through. And my circumstances had drastically changed that day.

1303
02:07:06.78 --> 02:07:15.78
But my God had not. He was still the same God on August 2nd as he was on August 1st. His character hadn't changed.

1304
02:07:15.78 --> 02:07:20.78
And we went and sat on the couch and I've got a skinny window next to my door,

1305
02:07:20.78 --> 02:07:23.78
did in the other house that I lived in at the time.

1306
02:07:23.78 --> 02:07:26.78
I looked outside and my friends were from my small group were all standing outside.

1307
02:07:26.78 --> 02:07:31.78
I'm like, what the heck? Get in here. I need you in here.

1308
02:07:31.78 --> 02:07:40.78
And the neighbor next door was from New York, very proper. And he's like, oh no, you don't go in there. You give them time.

1309
02:07:40.78 --> 02:07:44.78
And so they came in and we just talked about Mark and tried to process it.

1310
02:07:44.78 --> 02:07:48.78
And we cried and prayed and cried and cried.

1311
02:07:48.78 --> 02:07:54.78
They stayed for a couple hours and it was probably about 11 o'clock and everybody had left.

1312
02:07:54.78 --> 02:08:00.78
My son Christopher was still there. He served in the Marines. He was in Okinawa for five years or plus.

1313
02:08:00.78 --> 02:08:08.78
He met his wife over there and she, before they had five kids, would go home every year for six weeks.

1314
02:08:08.78 --> 02:08:16.78
And my daughter and my daughter-in-law had both just lost babies the year before at five and a half months in their pregnancy,

1315
02:08:16.78 --> 02:08:20.78
which is pretty unusually, lose a child that far along.

1316
02:08:20.78 --> 02:08:24.78
And of course our first thought was, oh no, no more lost, no more babies.

1317
02:08:24.78 --> 02:08:26.78
They were just both three months in their pregnancy.

1318
02:08:26.78 --> 02:08:30.78
And so he had decided to protect her to not tell her what was going on.

1319
02:08:30.78 --> 02:08:33.78
He knew that she'd be back home before the funeral.

1320
02:08:33.78 --> 02:08:40.78
And how he did that, struggling with probably the toughest pain he's ever known,

1321
02:08:40.78 --> 02:08:43.78
and not tell his wife and carry on conversations, is beyond me.

1322
02:08:43.78 --> 02:08:50.78
But he said, Mom, I'm going to stay here tonight. I said, thank you, son.

1323
02:08:50.78 --> 02:08:56.78
He said, I'm going to try to get some sleep. I'm like, OK, long noon, there was no way sleep was coming to me.

1324
02:08:56.78 --> 02:09:02.78
And I just wanted somebody to hold me and tell me it's going to be OK. We'll get through this.

1325
02:09:02.78 --> 02:09:07.78
At that point I'd been a widow for 12 years, and so there was nobody there.

1326
02:09:07.78 --> 02:09:13.78
And I remember thinking, OK, God's promised to be a husband of the widow and a father to the fatherless.

1327
02:09:13.78 --> 02:09:16.78
I know where my strength is going to come.

1328
02:09:16.78 --> 02:09:20.78
And so I went and grabbed my Bible and just opened it and opened to Psalms 27.

1329
02:09:20.78 --> 02:09:22.78
That's right where it plopped open.

1330
02:09:22.78 --> 02:09:26.78
It said, Lord is my light and my salvation. Whom shall I fear?

1331
02:09:26.78 --> 02:09:30.78
The Lord is the strength of my life. Of whom shall I be afraid?

1332
02:09:30.78 --> 02:09:37.78
When the wicked came against me to eat up my flesh, my enemies and my foes, they stumbled and they fell.

1333
02:09:37.78 --> 02:09:42.78
Though an army may rise against me, I will not fear.

1334
02:09:42.78 --> 02:09:51.78
The war may come against me, and I read that going, oh my goodness, did you write this today for me for my first circumstances?

1335
02:09:51.78 --> 02:09:59.78
And the end of it says, I would have lost hope if I had not believed I'd see the goodness of the Lord and the land of the living.

1336
02:09:59.78 --> 02:10:05.78
Wait on the Lord. Be of good courage, and I will strengthen your heart.

1337
02:10:05.78 --> 02:10:09.78
Wait, I stand, Lord, and I close my Bible and I saw that courage thing again.

1338
02:10:09.78 --> 02:10:14.78
I saw that the courage angel at the beginning of the night. Now God's reminding me again, courage.

1339
02:10:14.78 --> 02:10:16.78
I'm like, I got it, Lord.

1340
02:10:16.78 --> 02:10:22.78
And as I sat there and was praying, I've never audibly heard God speak, but in my thoughts he said,

1341
02:10:22.78 --> 02:10:31.78
I want you to read this at Mark's funeral. I want you to give everybody else the same hope that I've given you.

1342
02:10:31.78 --> 02:10:35.78
As I said, I was a rebel in my 20s, and my teenagers too.

1343
02:10:35.78 --> 02:10:40.78
God says he hates seven things, and I'd done six of them. I was faithful in my marriage.

1344
02:10:40.78 --> 02:10:48.78
You can go read the rest of them. I don't want to get into all that, but I've learned that if he asked me to do something, to just obey and do it.

1345
02:10:48.78 --> 02:10:51.78
It may not make any sense. He tells us his ways are not our ways.

1346
02:10:51.78 --> 02:10:56.78
But I'm sure I kind of was like a teenager and kind of went, are you kidding me, God?

1347
02:10:56.78 --> 02:11:02.78
It's my son's funeral. I don't know if I'll throw up or pass out. I don't know what I'll do.

1348
02:11:02.78 --> 02:11:10.78
And I pause and I say, I will walk through whatever doors you open, thinking it just meant to speak at Mark's funeral.

1349
02:11:10.78 --> 02:11:15.78
I know that if God would have told me what he had in store in all the different places that I'd be,

1350
02:11:15.78 --> 02:11:20.78
at one point I spoke in front of a million people in the mall in Washington, D.C.

1351
02:11:20.78 --> 02:11:24.78
And I was terrified, terrified to speak in front of people.

1352
02:11:24.78 --> 02:11:29.78
The preschool and kindergarten, we had two programs a year, one at Christmas and one at the kindergarten graduation.

1353
02:11:29.78 --> 02:11:34.78
I would literally hold the microphone with both hands and it'd still be bouncing all over,

1354
02:11:34.78 --> 02:11:37.78
because I was terrified to be in front of people.

1355
02:11:37.78 --> 02:11:41.78
So this was not my comfort zone. This wasn't something I'm like, oh yeah, I'm such a great speaker.

1356
02:11:41.78 --> 02:11:44.78
Yeah, this would be awesome. I'm like, okay.

1357
02:11:44.78 --> 02:11:51.78
And to see what he's done and the toughest thing that I could go through in life

1358
02:11:51.78 --> 02:12:00.78
and how he's taken that, taken Mark's Royce's story to continue to impact people and change the world

1359
02:12:00.78 --> 02:12:03.78
is nothing but a miracle.

1360
02:12:03.78 --> 02:12:11.78
But again, the toughest pain I've ever known, you know, you can't avoid pain.

1361
02:12:11.78 --> 02:12:16.78
You've got to walk right through the middle of it. You can't go around it over it.

1362
02:12:16.78 --> 02:12:21.78
You can't get stuck in it because then you don't heal and you don't get to the healthier side.

1363
02:12:21.78 --> 02:12:28.78
But all the reading I've done on grief that said that's the toughest thing you could ever go through is the instant death of a child.

1364
02:12:28.78 --> 02:12:35.78
And I would have to agree with that. You know, granted, my husband wasn't the love of my life that I'd been married to for 50 years,

1365
02:12:35.78 --> 02:12:39.78
but much tougher, much tougher.

1366
02:12:39.78 --> 02:12:48.78
But so proud of Mark. I look forward to that day when I do get to see him again, give him another big hug, you know,

1367
02:12:48.78 --> 02:12:52.78
kick him in the butt and say, okay, why did you not tell us you were married?

1368
02:12:52.78 --> 02:13:00.78
But if I know anything, I know God doesn't waste pain, you know.

1369
02:13:00.78 --> 02:13:04.78
If we allow him, he will take that and use that for his glory.

1370
02:13:04.78 --> 02:13:11.78
And, you know, in his wisdom, he doesn't have in me, I'm not flying planes going, oh, well, yeah, it's just because I'm so good at this.

1371
02:13:11.78 --> 02:13:14.78
That's why it's working. It's like, no, no, you don't understand.

1372
02:13:14.78 --> 02:13:19.78
I don't have any skills or talents to be a public speaker, never taking classes on it.

1373
02:13:19.78 --> 02:13:25.78
You know, it's just going through that life experience.

1374
02:13:25.78 --> 02:13:29.78
And really, what am I going to be afraid of? Mark ran into the line of fire?

1375
02:13:29.78 --> 02:13:39.78
How many times just on his final day, I'm going to be afraid of speaking in front of people? Yeah, I don't think so.

1376
02:13:39.78 --> 02:13:50.78
The, as I mentioned in the beginning, you know, basically, as soon as we found out that you had been notified, you know, we get the word,

1377
02:13:50.78 --> 02:14:01.78
and then guys start calling, calling you to talk to you. And it's actually all happening from my, I have an office in the tactical operations center with the direct landline to America.

1378
02:14:01.78 --> 02:14:14.78
And so guys are coming in, calling from there. And again, our attitude was, we're going to have to be consoling, you know, Mark's mom.

1379
02:14:14.78 --> 02:14:23.78
And it was literally the opposite. It was literally the opposite. You know, it was my guys that needed consoling.

1380
02:14:23.78 --> 02:14:30.78
You were the one that was saying, you know, what do you need? What can I send you? What do you, how can I help you guys?

1381
02:14:30.78 --> 02:14:43.78
And I mean, so it was like this courage that you had gotten the message on you immediately put into action.

1382
02:14:43.78 --> 02:15:08.78
And then it was just for us to be able to talk to you, the guys talking to you and hearing your voice and your encouragement is what allowed guys to be able to say,

1383
02:15:08.78 --> 02:15:22.78
okay, you know, we can move forward. And, and, you know, that scene of coming out of Charlie Med and seeing all those soldiers and Marines just lined up and, you know, that's like,

1384
02:15:22.78 --> 02:15:30.78
sometimes people will attempt to bait me into saying something negative about the army of the Marine Corps and they can't do it.

1385
02:15:30.78 --> 02:15:48.78
Nothing but love for those guys. When did you, so we sent guys home, guys came home with Mark, you know, guys escorted Mark home.

1386
02:15:48.78 --> 02:15:54.78
When did you start meeting the guys from the task unit from Charlie between from task unit bruiser?

1387
02:15:54.78 --> 02:16:06.78
And it was, excuse me, I think it was the majority of you guys, it was when you came back from that deployment.

1388
02:16:06.78 --> 02:16:12.78
I yesterday were at the funeral and I was like, who spoke at Mark's funeral?

1389
02:16:12.78 --> 02:16:24.78
I'm like, how can you not remember your son's ceremony and who spoke and I remember being in another one in the same. It was at the chapel there on North Island.

1390
02:16:24.78 --> 02:16:32.78
I remember being later at another funeral there. I'm like, did we have Mark's gasket in here? I don't remember. I'm like, but I think just part of that, it's too much.

1391
02:16:32.78 --> 02:16:35.78
So you just don't remember it.

1392
02:16:35.78 --> 02:16:45.78
So I don't, I know Bobby Gasoff. At first that was his Mark's swim buddy and yeah, man, that's a pretty tight connection with your swim buddy.

1393
02:16:45.78 --> 02:16:50.78
And they weren't going to send him at first because they said, no, he's in too much pain. This is not who we send.

1394
02:16:50.78 --> 02:16:53.78
And of course now they've learned that that is.

1395
02:16:53.78 --> 02:17:07.78
And they said Commodore Pibus at the time, now Admiral Pibus was on our doorstep the next morning. And you know, Sean, you know, what a compassionate, caring man.

1396
02:17:07.78 --> 02:17:16.78
And again, I still don't even at that point didn't understand the ranks. I knew Admiral was something special, but an admiral showing up on my doorstep.

1397
02:17:16.78 --> 02:17:19.78
Granted, he was Commodore. Would he have been an admiral as a Commodore?

1398
02:17:19.78 --> 02:17:21.78
No, he was a captain.

1399
02:17:21.78 --> 02:17:28.78
I always had the hardest time with the Commodore thing. I'm like, yeah, it's like a position, not a rank position, not a rank.

1400
02:17:28.78 --> 02:17:37.78
But he was there at the door. And I remember them saying, what else can we do for you? I'm like, give me Bobby Gasoff. I want Bobby here.

1401
02:17:37.78 --> 02:17:46.78
And so they did get Bobby home. I think he might have been in the Philippines at the time he stayed with me. He and his wife stayed with us for a week.

1402
02:17:46.78 --> 02:17:53.78
But I don't even remember who the other one was. I know later that Brian Yarbo told me he was one of them that escorted Mark home.

1403
02:17:53.78 --> 02:17:56.78
And I want to say, was Jason Hogan the other one or do you remember?

1404
02:17:56.78 --> 02:18:01.78
I think so. Yeah. We sent a few, it was a few guys. It was a few guys we sent home.

1405
02:18:01.78 --> 02:18:02.78
Yeah.

1406
02:18:02.78 --> 02:18:11.78
And then obviously we sent guys home with Mike too. And when guys came home with Mikey, they were coming home like, we knew that they weren't coming back because it was the end of deployment.

1407
02:18:11.78 --> 02:18:12.78
Right.

1408
02:18:12.78 --> 02:18:21.78
I can't remember exactly which guys went with Mark and which guys went with Mikey because some of them came back.

1409
02:18:21.78 --> 02:18:31.78
Right. And it was pretty close. It was like 7, 7 12 weeks. But I think the majority of that started by phone calls and emails while you guys were still deployed.

1410
02:18:31.78 --> 02:18:41.78
You know, I remember thinking, oh my gosh, I can't make any decisions. My brain is mush. Holy cow. Those guys are in combat.

1411
02:18:41.78 --> 02:18:57.78
They've got life or death decisions they've got to make. And once I realized having Mark's brothers in our home for the week, wow, you guys love Mark as much as we did and you were hurting just as, and that's how I'm like, oh, the brotherhood thing, I got it now.

1412
02:18:57.78 --> 02:19:06.78
It makes sense. And so my concern for you guys is you're in that combat zone. You're still going out on patrol.

1413
02:19:06.78 --> 02:19:17.78
Man, how are you guys going to deal with this? How are you guys going to process and stay safe? You know, and you, you know, I think it was late for was the one I'm like, you guys go back out there.

1414
02:19:17.78 --> 02:19:26.78
You go get some, you know, don't don't hang in your rooms and, you know, Mark would want you to continue the mission.

1415
02:19:26.78 --> 02:19:36.78
But that's really when those relationships started. I got a copy of the Charlie Batoon picture and I'd say, okay, who's the one on the left? And I'd write the name down.

1416
02:19:36.78 --> 02:19:48.78
Okay, the tall guy in the middle, who's that? And of course they gave me their name names. And then they talk about Biff or I'm like, I don't have a Biff on the sheet. Who's Biff?

1417
02:19:48.78 --> 02:20:04.78
You know, and then I learned, okay, most of them have other names that they go by. But and I get phone calls even from some of the moms of the guys, you know, checking on me and I knew, I didn't know I was going to start a foundation.

1418
02:20:04.78 --> 02:20:17.78
But we had a lot of support up to the funeral. And then I live in Arizona. I'm not near a base. I'm not here, you know, San Diego or, you know, the rest of the community is or major part of it.

1419
02:20:17.78 --> 02:20:26.78
But once funerals over there, there was nothing. I mean, other than talking to you guys over there, it just, you know, it stopped.

1420
02:20:26.78 --> 02:20:36.78
And I'm like, oh, cred, well, it's just starting for me now. The process, the journey of grief is just starting. And I've never been one to feel sorry for myself.

1421
02:20:36.78 --> 02:20:46.78
I was like, okay, I can't change anything you think for myself, but I can change it so nobody else has to go through without having support there. Somebody that knows what it's like.

1422
02:20:46.78 --> 02:20:53.78
So when I got the call that Mikey had died, I knew I had to be there. I didn't know what I was going to do, but I just knew I had to be there.

1423
02:20:53.78 --> 02:21:05.78
And then that was about the time, you know, the first ones were starting to come back home. And I'm like, man, I got to be there for my boys, not to be, oh my gosh, there's poor Mark's mom.

1424
02:21:05.78 --> 02:21:10.78
But to say, woohoo, the rest of my boys are home. You know, thank you, thank you.

1425
02:21:10.78 --> 02:21:21.78
And, you know, so was here and then came over for the funeral. I remember coming over and it was the same hotel where they'd put us up for Mark's funeral.

1426
02:21:21.78 --> 02:21:29.78
Same black vehicles, I don't know, it was the exact same, but, you know, that black SUV that you guys have. And I was standing down there that morning,

1427
02:21:29.78 --> 02:21:41.78
giving, you know, Sally and the family big hugs and said, I'm so sorry. And Admiral McGuire came down and asked how I was doing.

1428
02:21:41.78 --> 02:21:48.78
So, hanging in there. And he said, we want you to go in the vehicle with the family.

1429
02:21:48.78 --> 02:21:54.78
And I'm like, oh, no, no, no, no, I'm not here. This is not about Mark. This is not about me at all. I'm just here to support the family.

1430
02:21:54.78 --> 02:22:02.78
And they said, exactly, you know, and almost a panic, you know, here we got another one, you know, we thought we were good for a while.

1431
02:22:02.78 --> 02:22:09.78
And now, seven weeks later, we got another one. And he said, exactly, that's why we want you in the vehicle to support them.

1432
02:22:09.78 --> 02:22:19.78
I'm like, okay. So now I'm in the vehicle reliving, going back up to Fort Roast Cranes, same casket Mark was buried in, same place.

1433
02:22:19.78 --> 02:22:27.78
Although now, I know what it's like to get the folded flag. I know what it's to be done with the funeral and start that grieving process.

1434
02:22:27.78 --> 02:22:33.78
I'm out of just, you know, the little bit of the wound that was starting to heal was now ripping open.

1435
02:22:33.78 --> 02:22:38.78
But still, I knew it was the right thing. I knew that's what we're supposed to be to support this family, just to be there.

1436
02:22:38.78 --> 02:22:47.78
I didn't have anything planned. I didn't, you know, just to be there. And that's why I tell people all the time, when someone's grieving, just be there.

1437
02:22:47.78 --> 02:22:53.78
Don't worry about what you should say, what you shouldn't say, should I take anything, should I not take anything, just be there.

1438
02:22:53.78 --> 02:23:01.78
It means so much to have someone else there with you. If they want to talk about it, they'll probably open up and start talking about it.

1439
02:23:01.78 --> 02:23:08.78
You don't need to worry. You know, it's not like I don't remember that, you know, I had a son, Mark, and what happened to him.

1440
02:23:08.78 --> 02:23:14.78
But it's so important to be there. And that was really the first family that we supported.

1441
02:23:14.78 --> 02:23:22.78
You know, we got pretty close to the Montsour family. And, you know, Sally just passed away a couple months ago.

1442
02:23:22.78 --> 02:23:30.78
And so we were there again, you know, to be able to support and honor Mikey. But because I love that family, I understand their sacrifice.

1443
02:23:30.78 --> 02:23:37.78
And that's really what started the America's Mighty Warriors process, thinking.

1444
02:23:37.78 --> 02:23:46.78
And then I would just happen to be in Washington, D.C. when J. Redmond was there, you know, before even the note was posted on the door of, you know,

1445
02:23:46.78 --> 02:23:54.78
don't feel sorry for me. If you're coming in here to feel sorry for me, I earned these wounds doing what I, you know, love doing and don't, I don't need your sympathy.

1446
02:23:54.78 --> 02:24:03.78
I was in the hospital when Dan Knotsen was brought down from surgery. I just happened to be in Washington, D.C.

1447
02:24:03.78 --> 02:24:12.78
So these things just kept happening. That is my spiritual gift is to be an encourager and, you know, to support people.

1448
02:24:12.78 --> 02:24:18.78
And so that's where my strength, that's where I work well when I'm doing those things.

1449
02:24:18.78 --> 02:24:25.78
And then after a while, I'm like, ah, okay, I get it. I think there's a mission ahead. I don't think I'm just supposed to do this once or twice.

1450
02:24:25.78 --> 02:24:33.78
And, you know, that's when I'm like, okay, I can't continue to afford to fund this on my own dime. So we really do need to.

1451
02:24:33.78 --> 02:24:44.78
So officially we started the foundation in 2008. And the name of it, America's Mighty Warriors, the meaning of the name Mark means Mighty Warrior.

1452
02:24:44.78 --> 02:24:46.78
You know, he definitely lived up to his name.

1453
02:24:46.78 --> 02:24:49.78
Didn't you get that name from like a menu or something?

1454
02:24:49.78 --> 02:24:52.78
Great. Did Mark put that in your head to tell me that?

1455
02:24:52.78 --> 02:24:56.78
I think he told me a long time ago. He's always like, great, you got my name from a menu, mom.

1456
02:24:56.78 --> 02:24:57.78
That's what it is, right?

1457
02:24:57.78 --> 02:25:03.78
And it was. It was from a menu. As I mentioned, I'd already gone through the divorce. I was by myself here. I'm having this baby.

1458
02:25:03.78 --> 02:25:07.78
I have a three and a half year old, two year old, and now another little one.

1459
02:25:07.78 --> 02:25:15.78
Of course, back then you stayed three days in the hospital. That was common. It was rare that they let you go before that.

1460
02:25:15.78 --> 02:25:19.78
And they always ask, do you have small children and do you have help?

1461
02:25:19.78 --> 02:25:23.78
I'm like, yes, I have small children. No, I have no help.

1462
02:25:23.78 --> 02:25:30.78
And I knew that they heard two heartbeats. I knew that I knew that I knew I was having twin girls.

1463
02:25:30.78 --> 02:25:34.78
So I had names picked out for girls, but no boy names.

1464
02:25:34.78 --> 02:25:40.78
And they came in the day after he was born and said, you got to go home. We need your bed.

1465
02:25:40.78 --> 02:25:46.78
And I'm like, buh-buh, I don't have help. And I've smoked in there like, sorry.

1466
02:25:46.78 --> 02:25:49.78
So they said, you've got to name the baby before you go home.

1467
02:25:49.78 --> 02:25:53.78
And no one to discuss it with, no one to figure it out.

